simplify 😄 
```python
def get(self, key):
    try:
        return self.session.kv[key]
    except KeyError:
        return
```

@dfdeshom Thanks for pointing that out! I'm still confused by it though, since later in the file there are a couple lines like:

```python
try: time.sleep(0.1)
except NotImplementedError: pass
```

which again imply that somehow `time.sleep()` is going to raise a `NotImplementedError`, which is strange.

this seems to be getting longer/more complicated than it needs to be. Can't we just use

```
  // Check whether this node is before node n in the graph.
  bool isBefore(Node* n) {
    ONNX_ASSERT(n != nullptr);
    ONNX_ASSERT(n->inGraphList());
    for (Node * p = next(); p != nullptr; p = p->next()) {
      if (p == n) {
        return true;
      }
    }
    return false;
  }
```
